---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import "@fancyapps/ui/dist/fancybox/fancybox.css";

// Import all images from the pottery folder
const imageModules = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "../images/pottery/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif,webp}",
  { eager: true }
);

// Convert to array and extract label from filename
const images = Object.entries(imageModules).map(([path, module]) => {
  const filename = path.split("/").pop() || "";
  const label = filename.replace(/\.(jpeg|jpg|png|gif|webp)$/i, "");

  return {
    src: module.default,
    label,
    filename,
  };
});

// Sort images alphabetically by label
images.sort((a, b) => a.label.localeCompare(b.label));
---

<BaseLayout title="Pottery" sideBarActiveItemID="pottery">
  <div class="mb-5 flex justify-between items-start">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Pottery</div>
    <button id="sidebar-toggle" class="btn btn-sm btn-ghost hidden lg:flex gap-2" title="Toggle sidebar">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><line x1="9" y1="3" x2="9" y2="21"/></svg>
      <span class="toggle-text">Hide sidebar</span>
    </button>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    I throw on the wheel and experiment with making my own glazes in my home studio. My favorite things to make are big vases and mugs. I'm drawn to nature-inspired textures - mosses, mushrooms, organic geometry - and I like building up lots of layers in both glaze and surface design. Lately I've been exploring ways to incorporate electronics into ceramic forms.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-6 flex gap-3">
    <a class="btn btn-primary gap-2" href="https://instagram.com/dorion_ceramics" target="_blank">
